theorem isOpen_of_isClosed_and_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP1 : Topology.P1 (X := X) A) :
    IsOpen A := by
  -- From the hypotheses we have the equality `closure (interior A) = A`.
  have hEq :=
    Topology.closure_interior_eq_self_of_closed_and_P1
      (X := X) (A := A) hClosed hP1
  -- Since `interior A` is open, the equality implies that `A` itself is open.
  have hOpenInt : IsOpen (interior (A : Set X)) := isOpen_interior
  simpa [hEq] using hOpenInt
